bb-cli/Commands/bb-create.title: bb create
bb-cli/Commands/bb-create.description: bb create can be used to create all kinds of blocks!

bb-cli/Commands/bb-exec.title: bb exec
bb-cli/Commands/bb-exec.description: bb exec lets you run system commands inside all blocks' directories in one go.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-init.title: bb init
bb-cli/Commands/bb-init.description: The 'bb init' command can be employed to create and register an appblock.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-log.title: bb log
bb-cli/Commands/bb-log.description: bb log command reads and displays logs related to live blocks.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-login.title: bb login
bb-cli/Commands/bb-login.description: bb login lets you log into Appblock/ block Registry.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-ls.title: bb ls
bb-cli/Commands/bb-ls.description: To display the block and its current statuses.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-pull.title: bb pull
bb-cli/Commands/bb-pull.description: Pull command is used pull new blocks into an app.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-push.title: bb push
bb-cli/Commands/bb-push.description: To push block code to source control.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-push-config.title: bb push-config
bb-cli/Commands/bb-push-config.description: To push the AppBlock config to registry.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-stop.title: bb stop
bb-cli/Commands/bb-stop.description: The 'bb stop' command will stop all running ui blocks and also kill the emulator.

bb-cli/Commands/bb-sync.title: bb sync
bb-cli/Commands/bb-sync.description: The 'bb sync' command can be used to convert existing projects that were not built as blocks, to appblock projects.

intro.title: Blocks Architecture
intro.description: “As business needs change, organizations must be able to deliver innovation quickly and adapt applications dynamically — reassembling capabilities from inside and outside the enterprise. To do this, organizations must understand and implement the “composable enterprise.” – Gartner

SDK/js-sdk.title: @appblocks/js-sdk
SDK/js-sdk.description: @appblocks/js-sdk provides the essential packages to facilitate Appblocks features across Appblocks applications.

SDK/node-sdk.title: @appblocks/node-sdk
SDK/node-sdk.description: This includes the server-side libraries used by applications using Appblocks services.

Spaces.title: Spaces
Spaces.description: Space is where you as an organization collaborate, manage access, subscriptions, licenses and track your sales and purchases. Track and manage everything related to Appblocks in one space. Helps your organizations and teams to collaboratively work on applications and blocks and allows you to manage accesses of all these, all in one workspace.

types-of-blocks.description: We have predefined types for blocks in the registry. Each type refers to where and how it is utilised. Following is the list of Block Types available.
